<h4 id="TD_unit" class="level3">Unit and stoichiometry</h4>

<p class="item">
  Strictly speaking, equilibrium constants and, thus, binding constants, are defined based on relative activities and are therefore unitless. For solutions, mostly absolute concentrations instead of relative activities are considered and, accordingly,
  the association constants based on concentration have units as M<sup>-x</sup>.
  <a href="#t1">Table 1</a>
  gives an overview about common host-guest complex stoichiometry and the corresponding units.
  <br>
</p>

